\begin{cases}
x^2-4 &\quad \text{if } x \ge -4, \\
x + 3 &\quad \text{otherwise},
\end{cases}
\]then for how many values of $x$ is $f(f(x)) = 5$?

solution:
To solve for $x$, we wish to eliminate $y$. Multiply the first equation by $2$ and add it to the second: \begin{align*}
(4x-2y) + (x+2y) &= 10+5\\
